public interface IAppointmentDataInterface extends IDataInterface

  • Method Details

    • createNewDrugDispenseRequest

      DrugDispenseRequest createNewDrugDispenseRequest(String drugName, int addQuantity)
      Creates a new drug dispense request with the specified drug name and quantity.
      Parameters:
      drugName - the name of the drug to be included in the request.
      addQuantity - the quantity of the drug to be requested.
      Returns:
      a new instance of DrugDispenseRequest initialized with the given parameters.

    • readAppointmentOutcomesFromCSV

      ArrayList<AppointmentOutcome> readAppointmentOutcomesFromCSV()
      Reads appointment outcomes from a CSV file and returns them as a list of AppointmentOutcome objects.
      Returns:
      A list of AppointmentOutcome objects representing the outcomes of various appointments.

    • writeAppointmentsToCsv

      void writeAppointmentsToCsv(List<AppointmentInformation> appointments)
      Writes a list of appointment information to a CSV file.
      Parameters:
      appointments - the list of AppointmentInformation objects to be written to the CSV file.

    • writeAppointmentOutcomeToCSV

      void writeAppointmentOutcomeToCSV(AppointmentOutcome outcome)
      Writes the outcome of a specific appointment to a CSV file.
      Parameters:
      outcome - The outcome of the appointment to be written to the CSV file. This includes appointment ID, patient ID, type of appointment, consultation notes, and prescribed medications.

    • writeAllAppointmentOutcomesToCSV

      void writeAllAppointmentOutcomesToCSV(ArrayList<AppointmentOutcome> appointmentOutcomes)
      Writes all appointment outcomes to a CSV file.
      Parameters:
      appointmentOutcomes - a list of AppointmentOutcome objects to be written to the CSV file

    • readAppointments

      List<AppointmentInformation> readAppointments()
      Reads the list of appointments from the storage system.
      Returns:
      a list of AppointmentInformation objects representing the appointments.

    • loadSchedule

      AppointmentSchedule loadSchedule(String date)
      Loads the appointment schedule for the given date.
      Parameters:
      date - The date for which the appointment schedule is to be loaded.
      Returns:
      The appointment schedule for the specified date.

    • writeScheduleToCSV

      void writeScheduleToCSV(AppointmentSchedule schedule, String date)
      Writes the given appointment schedule to a CSV file for the specified date.
      Parameters:
      schedule - the appointment schedule to be written to the CSV file
      date - the date for which the schedule is to be written

    • getStaffForSchedule

      Staff getStaffForSchedule(String staffId)
      Retrieves the Staff member associated with a given schedule based on the staff ID.
      Parameters:
      staffId - the alphanumerical ID of the staff member to retrieve.
      Returns:
      the Staff object that matches the provided staff ID.

    • getStaffNameByID

      String getStaffNameByID(String userId)
      Retrieves the name of a staff member based on their unique identifier.
      Parameters:
      userId - The unique identifier of the staff member.
      Returns:
      The name of the staff member corresponding to the provided userId. If the userId is not found, returns null.

    • getAllDateFile

      File[] getAllDateFile()
      Retrieves all files containing appointment scheduling data.
      Returns:
      an array of Files representing all stored appointment schedules.

    • initializeSchedule

      void initializeSchedule(String date)
      Initializes the appointment schedule for the specified date.
      Parameters:
      date - The date for which to initialize the schedule, formatted as YYYYMMDD.

    • checkScheduleExist

      boolean checkScheduleExist(String date)
      Checks if a schedule exists for the given date.
      Parameters:
      date - The date in "yyyyMMdd" format for which the schedule existence needs to be verified.
      Returns:
      true if a schedule exists for the given date, false otherwise.
